# SPA fallback — explicit allowlist instead of a catch-all so unknown paths
# return a real 404 rather than the SPA shell with HTTP 200. The catch-all
# pattern (/* /index.html 200) is a soft-404 SEO trap: Google can index the
# SPA shell under typo URLs and flag the site.
#
# Marketing pages emitted by `marketing/yarn build` are overlaid into docs/
# by the Netlify build (see netlify.toml). Netlify resolves static files
# before consulting _redirects, so /about/, /blog/, /pricing/, etc. always
# win as 200 pre-rendered HTML — these rules only fire for SPA-handled
# paths that don't ship a static file. Add a new entry here when adding a
# new top-level SPA route, otherwise it will 404 in production.
/share/*         /index.html  200
/ipsum           /index.html  200
/popup-auth      /index.html  200
/popup-callback  /index.html  200
